For outdoor games, some fun options for your family gathering could be:

1. Water Balloon Toss: Divide the players into pairs and give each pair a water balloon. The pairs stand facing each other a few feet apart. They toss the water balloon back and forth, taking a step back after each successful catch. The last pair with an unbroken water balloon wins.

2. Three-Legged Race: Pair up players and have them stand side by side, with their arms around each other's shoulders and their adjacent legs tied together. Mark a finish line and have the pairs race to the finish line without falling or breaking their connection. The first pair to cross the finish line wins.

3. Cornhole: Set up two cornhole boards with bean bags. Each player takes turns throwing bean bags towards the boards, aiming to get them through the hole or on the board for points. The player or team with the most points at the end of the game wins.

Regarding delicious recipes for a barbecue party, I apologize but I'm currently facing issues retrieving the recipe recommendations. However, you can browse through various barbecue recipes on the Yummly website or app for a wide range of options.
